k without initialization, but a null global settings file might lead to a Null Pointer Exception. Initialization requires Plexus injection. However, a generated test could still focus on testing `Xpp3Reader/Writer` and `SettingsUtils`, even if not on the builder itself. I'm questioning what \\\\\\\"meaningful coverage\\\\\\\" truly means here.\\\\n\\\\n**Finalizing JSON structure**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering the final JSON setup, which should indicate \\\\\\\"no_action\\\\\\\" in the summary, and resolve with the POM specifying maven-model, plexus-utils, and plexus-container-default. I'm keeping it straightforward since normal usage involves a plain settings model alongside an XPP3 reader/writer, without any external services. \\\\n\\\\nI need to decide on whether to leave \\\\\\\"agent_guidance\\\\\\\" empty or include it as an optional field that expects a string. There are some risks to note too, primarily with the DefaultMavenSettingsBuilder potentially consulting real settings.\\\", \\\"thinkingSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"rs_0a261b07f1f2dd64016a417f3a489081969c8226a74b08ede9\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"reasoning\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\":[],\\\\\\\"encrypted_content\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"gAAAAABqQX9NhSHULagQ4u1oyAPi9ZVEs09XEF5thW9jI7PbdcM5gkOOD0CFOgE7a1sVuYy8GaZ_EIJFRLcRbkHay_8b4ajkN7IFgbPONsC_n0X72IHwvO565y26b52z0rdOVyAnbs5xgJU-aGuP4M5pwX8EnJOQEnEsAe3SA8Pwi6_AHPTf1mJgoVbbjj71KhgHGuLhTT2tTR3x0sv3dn0-87OhkmsRci43xYoa2H-_26CZbkRVHX4haKZOdLSnamQKrwq1MXDY783I9JvN5ypm5bffBHcWkndPXyNtusjX9ALkjSfgAPF122yCwkshhZfewKBTxQNZbA0QTiExZc3HdEEOvj3edr6B6yxZ2E5xzhN2WJMecQgYWrggSeI-tYsoLLiXhb0mOwBSNVoUBZq0Cd8Y96JxJshVmoDbxG1yRHce5OasrvUANTDMNZry-cIo0iT_g0ZLlAXseZ7kHYdI84euPIrLd1LMuAra2pXq3v0poYAfOFFXp93y3pljJvOnBIq72Ag3GjWK3KAvLyuUv-20z_P5coNi_cp4hbrndOY6Kmns7eyS3Oc7nfCySV534Y6_fLYD4sthaYOwD0ki6NGjuz0IDPSGowqLSQQNcyZrrXsvVjOqt91qKTloVt-CYXIM56kAsTtu4MFc1am7jzryH5jGP1YqP6F5H2UO9trdlr-7GHrdPNWe30goNcH7vdPHGiINWopaGelP-cIiZFuGBO9CLn_Lw_iqKfvLaFedM-ikfArQ7u