sidering Maven Setup Options**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nIn this scenario, setting up in home might be undesirable, but it shouldn't block processes entirely. I could set `maven.repo.local` to a temporary location. Using the public `buildSettings(File userSettingsFile, boolean)` method could work without initialization, but a null global settings file might lead to a Null Pointer Exception. Initialization requires Plexus injection. However, a generated test could still focus on testing `Xpp3Reader/Writer` and `SettingsUtils`, even if not on the builder itself. I'm questioning what \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"meaningful coverage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" truly means here.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Finalizing JSON structure**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm considering the final JSON setup, which should indicate \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"no_action\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in the summary, and resolve with the POM specifying maven-model, plexus-utils, and plexus-container-default. I'm keeping it straightforward since normal usage involves a plain settings model alongside an XPP3 reader/writer, without any external services. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI need to decide on whether to leave \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent_guidance\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" empty or include it as an optional field that expects a string. There are some risks to note too, primarily with the DefaultMavenSettingsBuilder potentially consulting real settings.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"action\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"no_action\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"org.apache.maven:maven-settings:2.0.6 is a Maven settings model/parser artifact; its POM declares the needed Maven model and Plexus utilities transitively, and normal meaningful tests can exercise Settings POJOs plus SettingsXpp3Reader/Writer without external services, Docker, or extra dependencies.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"deterministic_setup\\\\\\\": [],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"agent_guidance\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"risks\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"If generated tests choose to exercise DefaultMavenSettingsBuilder rather than the reader/writer APIs, that class consults Maven/user settings locations and may touch user-home defaults; such tests should isolate paths in test code, but this is not required for meaningful coverage.\\\\\\\"\\\\n  ]\\\\n}\\\", \\\"textSignature\\\": \\\"{\\\\\\\"v\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"msg_0a261b07f1f2dd64016a417f4d5b54819688ed1858c7b5f475\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"phase\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"final_answer\\\\\\\"}\\\"}], \\\"api\\\": \\\"openai-responses\\\", \\\"provider\\\": \\\"OCA\\\", \\\"model\\\": \\\"oca/gpt-5.5\\\", \\\"usage\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 1445, \\\"output\\\": 1323, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 33280, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"totalTokens\\\": 36048, \\\"cost\\\": {\\\"input\\\": 0, \\\"output\\\": 0, \\\"cacheRead\\\": 0, \\\"cacheWrite\\\": 0, \\\"total\\\": 0}}, \\\"stopReason\\\": \\\"stop\\\", \\\"timestamp\\\": 1782677304945, \\\"responseId\\\": \\\"resp_0a261b07f1f2dd64016a417f39702081969c7b07367cfdd8b8\\\"}, \\\"toolResults\\\": []}\\n[recv] agent_end\\n[send] get_state\\n[recv] get_state success\\n  sessionFile: ../../../../.pi/agent/sessions/--home-vjovanov-c-forge-forge2-graalvm-reachability-metadata-forge-local_repositories-forge_worktrees-2327-631f0e3d--/2026-06-28T20-07-36-718Z_019f0fd8-3a0e-7071-b92d-e23312135746.jsonl\\n  sessionId: 019f0fd8-3a0e-7071-b92d-e23312135746\\n[send] get_session_stats\\n[recv] get_session_stats success\\n  tokens: input=51830 output=3841 cacheRead=172544 cacheWrite=0 total=228215\\n\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.started\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_20\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/usr/bin/bash -lc 'rg -n \\\"FAILED|FAILURE:|What went wrong|Exception|Could not resolve|Failed to create Jar file|tck-build-logic|BUILD FAILED|Execution failed\\\" /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge2/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.apache.maven:maven-set