e might lead to a Null Pointer Exception. Initialization requires Plexus injection. However, a generated test could still focus on testing `Xpp3Reader/Writer` and `SettingsUtils`, even if not on the builder itself. I'm questioning what \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"meaningful coverage\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" truly means here.\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"summary_text\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"**Finalizing JSON structure**\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI'm considering the final JSON setup, which should indicate \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"no_action\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" in the summary, and resolve with the POM specifying maven-model, plexus-utils, and plexus-container-default. I'm keeping it straightforward since normal usage involves a plain settings model alongside an XPP3 reader/writer, without any external services. \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nI need to decide on whether to leave \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"agent_guidance\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" empty or include it as an optional field that expects a string. There are some risks to note too, primarily with the DefaultMavenSettingsBuilder potentially consulting real settings.\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}, {\\\"type\\\": \\\"text\\\", \\\"text\\\": \\\"{\\\\n  \\\\\\\"action\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"no_action\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"summary\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"org.apache.maven:maven-settings:2.0.6 is a Maven settings model/parser artifact; its POM declares the needed Maven model and Plexus utilities transitively, and normal meaningful tests can exercise Settings POJOs plus SettingsXpp3Reader/Writer without external services, Docker, or extra dependencies.\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"deterministic_setup\\\\\\\": [],\\\\n  \\\\\\\"agent_guidance\\\\\\\": \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\",\\\\n  \\\\\\\"risks\\\\\\\": [\\\\n    \\\\\\\"If generated tests choose to exercise DefaultMavenSettingsBuilder rather than the reader/writer APIs, that class consults Maven/user settings locations and may touch user-home defaults; such tests should isolate paths in test code, but this is not required for meaningful coverage.\\\\\\\"\\\\n